    movementSourcing:
      'Overwhelmingly in-house. Patek designs and manufactures its own movements in Geneva and is one of very few houses producing a full range of complications internally — time-only, perpetual calendars, split-seconds chronographs, minute repeaters, tourbillons, and the Grandmaster Chime. It moved off Lemania/ebauche chronograph bases to its own calibers (e.g. CH 29-535 PS). Mid-20th-century pieces did use outside ebauches (notably Jaeger-LeCoultre), but modern output is self-produced under the proprietary Patek Philippe Seal, which replaced the Geneva Seal for the brand in 2009.',
