      'Through the 2000s Panerai rode a wave of the big-watch trend and built a famously fervent collector base (the Paneristi). After the oversized-watch fashion cooled, the brand worked to broaden appeal with smaller 38-44mm cases, experimental materials (Carbotech, BMG-TECH, Goldtech, eSteel from recycled steel), long power reserves, and headline-grabbing concept pieces like the Lab-ID with a near-frictionless escapement. Today it remains one of the most distinctive design brands in watchmaking — beloved for its identity, debated for its finishing and value retention.',
