      "Baume & Mercier traces its roots to 1830, when brothers Louis-Victor and Célestin Baume opened a watchmaking comptoir, 'Frères Baume,' in Les Bois, a village in the Swiss Jura. The firm built an early reputation for precision, opening a London branch as 'Baume Brothers' in 1851 and racking up accuracy records and timekeeping-competition wins through the late 19th century — credentials that gave the eventual brand its claim to deep horological pedigree.",
      "The modern maison was born in 1918, when company director William Baume joined forces with Paul Mercier (born Paul Tchereditchenko) to found 'Baume & Mercier' in Geneva. The new firm leaned into Genevan watchmaking prestige and in 1919 earned the Poinçon de Genève (Geneva Seal), then the highest mark of finishing and quality available. The phi (φ) symbol in the logo nods to the Golden Ratio and the brand's pursuit of harmonious proportion. Mid-century highlights include sought-after 1940s two-register chronographs.",
      "Commercially, the brand passed through several hands: it came under Piaget's control in the 1960s, and in 1988 became part of the group that consolidated into Compagnie Financière Richemont, the Swiss luxury conglomerate that also owns Cartier, IWC and Jaeger-LeCoultre. Under Richemont, B&M was positioned as an accessible gateway to the group, launching the rectangular Art Deco-flavored Hampton (1994) and reviving its dodecagonal 1973 integrated-sports icon, the Riviera (designed by Jean-Claude Gueit), in 2021. The 2018 Clifton Baumatic — the brand's first true in-house movement — marked a serious bid for enthusiast credibility.",
      "In a major change, Richemont announced on January 22, 2026 that it had agreed to sell Baume & Mercier outright to Italy's Damiani Group, the family-owned jewelry house, in a private transaction expected to close in Summer 2026. Richemont cited Damiani's strong Italian footprint and multi-brand wholesale model as a better fit, and agreed to provide operational services for at least 12 months to ease the transition. The move ends a 38-year Richemont chapter and opens an uncertain but potentially energizing new one for the brand.",
