      "The catalog has expanded from the single Neptune into a tight six-model lineup, each with a clear job: Neptune (skin diver), Hydra (do-it-all sports diver, now GMT-capable), Hyperion (vintage GMT), Falcon (field watch), Astra (sporty-dress) and the Olympia automatic chronograph. Lorier is known for resisting the microbrand habit of endless one-off colorways, instead iterating models in numbered 'Series' (SII, SIII, SIV) with measured improvements like better bracelets (the Ternion) and movement upgrades.",
      "As of the mid-2020s Lorier is one of the most respected American microbrands, regularly cited in 'best microbrand' and 'best affordable diver' roundups. It remains small and independent, with popular references frequently selling out and a healthy, fairly value-retentive secondary market by microbrand standards.",
